as the most miserable man I have ever seen. It turned out to be one of his own performers! He had devised the entire prank himself without telling a soul. I felt foolish for being tricked, but I would not have traded places with that ringmaster for a thousand dollars. I cannot say for sure, but while there may be superior circuses, I have yet to encounter one. Regardless, it was perfectly satisfactory for me, and I will patronize it whenever I happen upon it.\n\nThat evening, we held our own performance, but only about twelve people attended—just enough to cover the costs. They laughed throughout the entire event, which angered the duke, and everyone departed before the show concluded, except for one boy who had fallen asleep."
